29/08/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Parliament must show it is not a prisoner of vested interests, Principle Deputy High Representative Lawrence Butler said on Monday (28 August), during a meeting with BiH Minister for Civil Affairs Safet Halilovic.
They focused on the new law on pharmaceuticals and medical devices, which the House of Representatives is to consider this week.
Butler suggested that the well being of consumers is taking a back seat to the influence of lobbyists, which he said could affect potential foreign investment in BiH.
In other news Monday, police discovered the largest marijuana plantation in the country.
Located in the village Zrvanj near Ljubinje, the market value of the crop was estimated at the 500,000 euros.
(OHR website, Fena, RTRS - 28/08/06)
